{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, AI has shown significant Page 2 of 29 Walter Int J Educ Technol High Educ (2024) 21:15 promise in providing timely interventions for children with special educational needs, enriching both their learning experiences and daily life (Zawacki-Richter et al., 2019).",
    "However, integrating AI into education is not without its challenges.",
    "It requires a systematic approach that takes into account societal structural conditions.",
    "Beyond algorithmic thinking, AI in education demands a focus on creativity and technology fluency to foster innovation and critical thought.",
    "This requires a paradigm shift in how education is approached in the AI era, moving beyond traditional methods to embrace more dynamic, interactive, and student-centered learning environments (Chiu et al., 2023)."
  ]
}